Ok so
"since if the swap worked, I would be waitlisted for all my classes and be below the minimum enrolled L&S unit requirement of one enrolled course"
This is not true. The way it works when you try to swap an enrolled class into a waitlisted class is:
You remain enrolled in the original class (16A) but you're also put on the waitlist for the class you're trying to swap into (188). This way, you basically hold your seat in the org. class while putting yourself on the waitlist for the other under the contract that once you get in the waitlisted class (188), you'd be automatically dropped from the org. (16A).

Including waitlisted/enrolled/swapped classes, how many units are you enrolled in? That's what matters, not the minimum unit..
Also if a class is full and you try to swap into it, you are put on the waitlist while still being enrolled in the original class.

I believe you'll still be on the waitlist, based on personal experience.

Also, it's a pending swap because you're waitlisted for 188. The system won't actually swap you unless/until you're enrolled. 

Once you're enrolled into 188 from the waitlist, the swap will be completed and you'll be dropped from ee16a (if you haven't dropped it already).
